      boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
      Implementations of the MissingAttributeDetail interface must override the equals method with the following semantics: Two MissingAttributeDetails (m1 and m2) are equal if: m1.getCategory().equals(m2.getCategory()) AND m1.getAttributeId().equals(m2.getAttributeId()) AND m1.getDataTypeId().equals(m2.getDataTypeId()) AND m1.getIssuer() == null && m2.getIssuer() == null OR m1.getIssuer().equals(m2.getIssuer()) AND m1.getAttributeValues() is pairwise equal to m2.getAttributeValues()

        public StdMutableMissingAttributeDetail(Identifier categoryIn,
                                Identifier attributeIdIn,
                                Identifier dataTypeIdIn,
                                java.lang.String issuerIn,
                                java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> attributeValuesIn)
        Creates a new StdMutableMissingAttributeDetail with the given Identifiers for the XACML Category, AttributeId, and DataType of the missing Attribute, and the given String Issuer. If not null, the Collection of AttributeValues is copied into the new StdMutableMissingAttributeDetail.
        Parameters:
        categoryIn - the Identifier representing the XACML Category of the missing Attribute
        attributeIdIn - the Identifier representing the XACML AttributeId of the missing Attribute
        dataTypeIdIn - the Identifier representing the XACML DataType of the missing AttributeValue
        issuerIn - the String representing the XACML Issuer (may be null)
        attributeValuesIn - the Collection of AttributeValues representing the expected AttributeValues for the missing Attribute

        public java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> getAttributeValues()
        Description copied from interface: MissingAttributeDetail
        Gets the Collection of AttributeValues that were expected for the Attribute that was missing. If there are no expected AttributeValues this method should return an empty list. The Collection returned should not be modified. Implementations are free to use unmodifiable Collections to enforce this.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        a Collection of AttributeValues that were expected for the Attribute that was missing.

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
